entries.title: Canada Pursues Private Options to Ease Healthcare Backlogs
entries.description: Ontario is the latest Canadian province turning to private clinics in an effort to address growing problems with the publicly funded healthcare system.

entries.title: Eritrean Troops Endanger Ethiopian Peace Deal
entries.description: A peace accord meant to end Ethiopia’s civil war is hitting a stumbling block, as troops from neighboring Eritrea who had been fighting on the side of the federal government have failed to withdraw, local and international officials say.

entries.title: Pressure Builds on Germany to Approve Tanks for Ukraine
entries.description: Pressure mounted on Germany to approve the transfer of its Leopard 2 battle tanks to Ukraine, a day after Western allies at a meeting failed to reach an agreement about sending armored vehicles.

entries.title: Ukraine's Winter Could Turn Against Russian Troops
entries.description: With Western-supplied uniforms and ‘trench candles,’ Ukrainian soldiers are seeking a cold-weather advantage.

entries.title: South Africa Seeks State Power Chief After CEO Says He Was Poisoned
entries.description: Eskom is buckling under debt and an aging coal-powered fleet, and its departing chief says criminal networks, corruption and government divisions thwarted his efforts.

entries.title: Chris Hipkins, Ex-Covid Minister, on Track to Become New Zealand's Next Leader
entries.description: Chris Hipkins, a lawmaker best known for serving as New Zealand’s Covid-19 minister, is poised to become the country’s next leader.
